caption: The food is flavorful. My friend got lunch for us. I didn’t know about the price. The amount is nice.
Hole in the wall restaurant.  Prices ok, and portions were good.  Delicious dumplings and beef chow fun.

I have lived in Hong Kong. There is no doubt that Lam's Kitchen would be popular even in HK for their beef tendon. It is served with rice or soup noodles -- you can't go wrong with either. Another classic they have mastered is beef ho fan (or stir fried beef noodles). 5/5

Everything is ridiculously good there. Wonton and brisket fun are most popular.
Service is quick for take out and sit in. Price is reasonable and servings are large that I usually have to take home half.

Super authentic Cantonese food - almost all customers speak Cantonese there so that says a lot about the restaurant.  I am pregnant and miss my comfort food so bad so I went there and ordered duck look fun (yep that is the name!) and porridge. Both tasted amazing! Generous portions as well.  They only do take-out because of COVID now.
Best food in Chinatown!

This place is pretty packed especially during lunch. I've been craving chow fun so I will risk COVID-19 for some. I've only tried two dishes. A dried chow fun, and chow fun with choy sum (gravy). Normally I don't like the one with gravy but in this case the one with gravy was great. The dry one was sub par. I will be back to try some of their other items. The restaurant was not very clean, people didn't really observe the social distancing protocol, and parking sucks. My rating is based off of the food because, well hey, I knew where I was looking to get food, Chinatown...
The look fun was good but really enjoyed the side order of wontons can't wait to go back
Very good food and friendly.
Great

Had duck and noodles soup. If looking for vietamese soup and not traditional Chinese food then ok. The area is a mix of pho and Chinese shops. This was first time there so not all uber driver's know what's good. Sadly I am all about traditional Korean and Chinese foods and not cheap noodles used in the soups. 3 stars is a gift. Chinatown is at least not as odorific as Chinatown Los Angeles. Which is very dirty. I heard that Chengdu taste is good sichuan foods.
Very flavorful dishes. So many choices.
Awesome and hearty meal, it was my 1st time eating here and definitely coming back.
Small place in Chinatown that serves very tasty food!

Known for their flat rice noodle. Order it with the beef stew. Don't order the bitter melon with beef, it is not consistent as to too salty. Their egg noodle is not make there but it taste great too, I believe they get fresh made noodle in the area.

I love their broth and the noodles itself. The service was fast and friendly. One of the reasons I'm giving them a 5 star review was that they stayed open and served me despite me arriving at their closing time (my bad). 👏

Unbelievable find recommended my family members. Amazing dumplings and dishes. You can't order anything wrong! A must stop! ❤️
Good services and foods are delicious. Especially the owner and employees are very nice to customers.
Good Hong Kong style food.

Fast service. One menu so quickly decide or yelp because they'll take it away for the next ppl that come in. Decent bathroom considering its Chinatown. Homemade noodles. Known for beef brisket soup. I ordered look fun with just choy sum. Broth is delicious.
Mini Chinese restaurant, taste good, reasonable price
Amazing noodles, definitely handmade, awesome flavor! Definitely recommend.

Food was delicious! Served with tea. But. Honestly that restroom there is horrible. Smells like an outhouse. The kitchen is right before it. They dont have anything organized. The restroom walls are very sticky, and I seriously didn't feel like eating there. But I did. Other that there service is good, the vibes. Everything but that restroom. Oof!

Pretty much an overcrowded hole in the wall with the best Chinese food.  If you don't mind dealing with the vagrants around Chinatown and waiting a while for table to eat delicious authentic Chinese food, come here.   Everything on the menu is good.
delicious beef brisket Wonton soup.
Beef & tendon noodle soup!
Great homestyle food!!
I love their look fun noodles with beef tendon and brisket! Just a great bowl of goodness!!!!!! Put the home made chili oil in to taste. Just awesome!

The beef chow funn is very good. Noodles are made fresh and you can taste the quality and difference. I would also recommend the won ton soups and the egg noodles. Ask the lady what you should get and her recommendations are spot on.

What a great little place in Chinatown for a noodle fix. Here they specialize in rice and egg noodle dishes that are made in house. Came in with a group of 7 and got their beef flank & tendon mien (8.99$), wonton mien (8.25$), and beef choysum chow fun (8.99$) and it was delicious. The portion size is amazing and the flavors were spot on. We had an order of wonton on the side (8.00$) to add it to the beef noodle soup and it was excellent. The service was also great. The servers were patient and attentive. Gave them an extra tip because they were so nice. The restaurant is small so you might have to wait a bit before if you come in a large group.
Amazing food. Must try if u visiting honolulu.
Food is good prices reasonable. Small place but seats turnover fast because service is fast. Noodles are made from rice and made in house.

Went there for quick lunch & despite being packed on a Sunday we were seated immediately.  Place was filled with locals; staff was very friendly & food was very reasonably priced & excellent!!! Son loved the dumplings!!!
Solid taste and solid portion. You can't go wrong
Big portions and low prices! Authentic Hong long noodles, very delicious.
My go-to for Jook (rice porridge with pork and century egg) and Cheung funn. It's something that I could never imitate, so I have no choice but to come here and eat!
Great soup!
Cheap Asian food that tasted pretty good for price wise.
Good authentic HK cantonese style comfort food.
Delicious comfort food
Great place for REAL Chinese food. I had the won ton noodle soup. It's very good!
So reasonable and delicious! Beef Choy Sum Chow Fun is a must!

Great food at good price. I really enjoyed the beef chow funn and the beef funn in soup. The flavors are great and prices are reasonable. Only thing it can get crowded quickly but people are usually in and out quite quickly.
A hidden gem in Chinatown Honolulu. Awesome food, reasonable prices

The rice noodle is so great. We enjoy the Chinese donut too. It’s very crispy outside and soft inside. The pepper in pork porridge is a little too much for me. The service is great. We see lots of local people enjoy their breakfast here.
never a bad meal, always consistent, staff works hard & very friendly, price for what you get makes it one of the best cheap eats on Oahu.
Great food!
Good, good food.
Walked pass by and noticed a long line waiting to go in to this tiny place.  So I waited and order a bowl of Duck  look Fun.   Now I can see why!  It was soo good.  Diffinatly going back again!

Really great local shop for noodle and wonton dishes.
Delicious food at good prices. Plenty to eat.  Proprietor is very likable and has a great sense of humor.  First timer? Try the Chow Fun with beef either in soup or on a plate.  Both excellent.
Good food, but limited seating, be prepared to have to wait.

Chinese comfort food at its finest! Service was fast and friendly. The atmosphere was inviting. Seating is minimal but turnover was fast. Parking may be an issue because it is in town. But, I will be going back a lot.

Simple HK style noodle dishes.  Small place and expect to wait during lunch hours.  Accepts credit card, which is a plus.  Not too many places in Chinatown do especially when they try to evade paying taxes.
Won ton mein awesome
More please!!!
Fantastic food, great service and very coZy atmosphere. Hot & sour soup best I've had in a long time If you are in the bay area dont miss this restaurant.
Loved the experience of this noodle soup ! Big bowl for the $, so delicious ! Would return for other menu items .
Awesome

I tried the bowl pictured on the menu... it was okay but not special. The broth was fine but not as flavorful as I would have liked. Call me "not a fan".
My favorite noodle spot so far. The prices are great. Especially so when you taste their food here. My favorites are the beef and tendion look fun and the wonton mein....
Had look fun fish soup.  Excellent!!

Great tasting food. Restaurant should find larger store.

Pretty tasty. Looks like they're mainly known for their soup and noodles of course. Do yourself a favor add some shrimp wonton to your soup. Very good. My kids had the chicken and green bean with rice and liked it quite a bit.
It was different

Loved it, their beef & tendon chow fun is always yummy, my mother's favorite is their beef & tendon look fun (noodle in soup). My 3 year old can finish half the plate of chow fun by himself. definitely will come again.
Excellent food
Very good flavor to the broth.
A Small restaurant  in chinatown. Very clean and cool place to eat. Food is very good.

Got to try their Look Fun rolls. You absolutely have eat the rolls with the peanut sauce, the sweet soy,  the Hoisin, and if you'd like a little kick add the garlic chili pepper . Try as well their very popular (shrimp) Wonton Look Fun. Only downside is finding parking, there is Mauna Kea Street Market parking lot or street parking.
(Translated by Google) I like the porridge here  (Original) 我很喜欢吃这里的粥

Came here with family and ordered beef brisket wonton over fun( wide noodles).  Totally happy and was in fun heaven. 5 stars Meat was mostly tender and flavorful.  Wontons had a nice texture and good flavor to soup too.  Noodles smooth and wonderful.  All at a great price.  We came around 1050 am right before it got over crowded with lunch run.  Super busy here and service is swift with no nonsense staff.  Tip: Ignore the attitude and just be thankfull for the food.

This place is a Great Hole in the wall that we were brought too about a year ago. Everything on the menu is reasonably priced fir tge amount of food you get. I never would've thought of trying this place, but now we come into Chinatown once a month to eat here after a stroll through Chinatown. Just remember that they have what's called Wet and Dry Noodles. So be sure to specify that to your server.
If you haven't eaten here you have been missing out

Small, cozy, efficient, and very clean restaurant. The staff was super friendly and eager to explain  items on the menu.  They even have picture menus and vegan options. The food was prepared quickly.  I enjoyed every bite.
Stars are for price, food taste and quick service
Great food.  Super busy for small shop.  Very nice rice soup and noodles

Delicious made from scratch Chinese Look Funn. Won Ton with Choi Sum on the side. Dry style beef Funn or gray style beef and choi sum Funn or in a soup. Crowded during lunch, but wait is reasonable. Very reasonable prices. Park in nearby municipal lots or take a bus or walk. Always fresh and delicious.

My favorite Chinese noodle restaurant on the island! This place has the most fresh chow fun noodles and this makes a huge difference! Try this place for their noodles and other chow fun restaurants will never taste the same. I highly recommend their black-been-sauce chow fun w/ beef or pork and also their wun tun mein! Street/public parking unfortunately.
Great place to get look fun. Love the texture and the sauces. The chili oil is fantastic!
Homemade noodle. Good soups. Love their chilli oil. Not so much customer service but the food always good.
Lam's makes the best "fun"  white fat noodle. The Chinese (from China) all patron this joint.  It is the best "fun" I ever had.  I like the "dry fry fun with beef" The porridge is excellent too.

Lam's Kitchen is located in Chinatown. They make their own look funn which you can buy by the pound. You can also dine and order things like won ton mein, beef brisket noodle, pork and thousand year old egg jook, or beef chow funn. It's a popular spot for the locals (mainly Chinese) during lunch because the prices are very reasonable. It's best to go before noon. They have English on their menu and there's another menu with some photos. You can get by without speaking the language and pointing at what you want to order.
Food is tasty and prepared very quickly!

Beef brisket and wonton noodles are really good here

Get your self a beef noodle fun. It's their best dish and I have yet to find a place that compares to it!!
Beef brisket and tendon with look fun is bomb. Be sure to try the chili oil concoction. The look fun roll with all the sauces is broke da mouth, too.
taste good & cheap

Authentic Chinese food. Fast service. Awesome prices.
Great food here at excellent prices. Limited seating available but takeout is an option.
Beef flank and tendon stew on rice or with noodle (can add wonton too), with their home-made secret spicy chili oil sauce, me and my friends love this place!!!
Delicious! Very friendly staff and moderate price.

The best beef and tendon soup ever. I get the dish without soup because it has more flavor but the beef is so soft it melts in your mouth. The look funn, which is a must order with your dish, is homemade, super soft, and seriously the best. Also, add wontons to the dish if you're not allergic to shrimp because their wontons are so simple yet so good. Best wontons I've had in Hawaii.
Fast, delicious, and adorable.
Beef flank and tendon with choy sum is my go to dish here.
A hidden gem in Chinatown. Amazing, consistent and tasty beef brisket and tendon look fun. Look fun is their specialty and I like to add wontons to their beef look fun soups for a great lunch.
Cheap and good. Noodle and beef are tender. We are a regular
One of my go-to downtown lunch spots. Beef brisket and tendon in look fun soup is a hearty and delicious.
